Advanced hybrid manufacturing of printed electronics represents a cutting-edge approach that combines traditional printing techniques with sophisticated additive manufacturing processes. 
This integrated technologies enables complex functionalities and diverse materials into the production of electronic components. 
<br>
<br>
<b> Our current research directions:</b>
<ul>
<li> <b> Design and development of smart and self-powered surfaces  </b> </li>
<li> <b> Development of reliable and durable surface structures for nanogenerators and solar cells  </b> </li>
<li> <b> Additively manufactured smart structures with embedding sensing capabilities </b> </li>
<li> <b> Scalable manufacturing of energy devices for IoT applications </b> </li>

